
Overview of noun spit

The noun spit has 4 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                         
1. spit, tongue -- (a narrow strip of land that juts out into the sea)
2. saliva, spit, spittle -- (a clear liquid secreted into the mouth by the salivary glands and mucous glands of the mouth; moistens the mouth and starts the digestion of starches)
3. spit -- (a skewer for holding meat over a fire)
4. spit, spitting, expectoration -- (the act of spitting (forcefully expelling saliva))

Overview of verb spit

The verb spit has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (11) spit, ptyalize, ptyalise, spew, spue -- (expel or eject (saliva or phlegm or sputum) from the mouth; "The father of the victim spat at the alleged murderer")
2. (1) spit, spit out -- (utter with anger or contempt)
3. sprinkle, spit, spatter, patter, pitter-patter -- (rain gently; "It has only sprinkled, but the roads are slick")
4. skewer, spit -- (drive a skewer through; "skewer the meat for the BBQ")
